 -- Sukochev Roman <leolikua@gmail.com>  Sun, 23 Oct 2011 01:33:00 +0200

notify-osd (0.9.32-0ubuntu3-leolik~ppa0) oneiric; urgency=low

  * Apply patch for notify-osd(0.9.32-0ubuntu3)
    Features:
    - Themes support (change color, width, height or other options of bubble )
    - Timeout ( "-t" option), work in this version 
    - Display notifications in different corners of the screen.
           type in console:
           $ gsettings set com.canonical.notify-osd gravity [number]
           where [number]:
           1 - top-right corner
           2 - middle-right
           3 - bottom-right corner
           4 - bottom-left corner
           5 - middle-left
           6 - top-left corner
    - Two options from Faheem Pervez:
           * bubble-prevent-fade: Stops the bubble from fading out when the mouse pointer hovers over it
           * bubble-close-on-click: Closes a notification when clicked on

 -- Sukochev Roman <leolikua@gmail.com>  Sun, 23 Oct 2011 01:33:00 +0200

